author: aconway
msg: QPID-2436: Fix cluster update of remote agents.
The v2key of cluster agents was not being passed as part of a cluster update.
This meant they were not being associated with the correct shadow connections on
the updatee. This caused inconsistencies that shut down the new broker.

author: aconway
msg: QPID-2436: Drop the vhost prefix in QMF V2keys.
- The prefix makes the keys extremely long and unreadable.
- In a standalone broker it adds nothing since its the same for every object.
- In a cluster you need a consistent ID for shadow connections on all brokers.
